Thomas Tighe (1829–15 June 1914) was an Irish Home Rule League politician.
He was elected as Member of Parliament (MP) for Mayo at the 1874 general election but was shortly after unseated. At the resulting by-election, he failed to regain the seat.He was High Sheriff of Mayo in 1879.
